The paper discusses real-time dense computer vision and SLAM for robotics, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also focuses on performance and accuracy benchmarking of SLAM systems, which is related to computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of synthetic RGB-D sequences with ground truth for comparison suggests an emphasis on artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the analysis of energy efficiency for different configurations relates to systems and control (cs.SY).
